<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880503-0042 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: John Fairfax Ltd. </HL><SO> </SO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   The management of Ms. and Sassy magazines has arranged financing to buy the two publications from John Fairfax Ltd., the Australian-based media group.    The price for the two New York-based magazines wasn't disclosed. Financing will be provided by a venture-capital group and State Bank of New South Wales in New York.    The new company acquiring the two magazines is Matilda Publications Inc. Sandra Yates, who was president of Fairfax in the U.S., is Matilda's president and chief executive officer; Anne Summers, who was Fairfax's U.S. vice president, is vice president.    In addition to raising capital to buy the magazines, Matilda also has secured working capital to continue building the magazines. Fairfax has been selling assets to cut the borrowing costs of its takeover last year by a member of the founding family. </TEXT></DOC>